
# Git & GitHub Commands

Step 1 - Go to your project folder
cd ~/path/"name of your folder"


## Step 2 - Create a README file (optional)


touch README.md
```

## Step 3 - Initialize Git

```bash
git init
```

## Step 4 - Add all files and folders

```bash
git add .
```

## Step 5 - Create your first commit

```bash
git commit -m "Initial commit"
```

## Step 6 - Rename the branch to `main`

```bash
git branch -M main
```

## Step 7 - Connect your GitHub repository

```bash
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPOSITORY.git
```

> If `origin` already exists:

```bash
git remote remove origin
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPOSITORY.git
```

## Step 8 - Upload your project to GitHub

```bash
git push -u origin main
```

---

# Update Your Project

## Stage all changes

```bash
git add .
```

## Commit your changes

```bash
git commit -m "Describe your changes"
```

## Push the changes

```bash
git push
```

---

# Remove a File

```bash
git rm filename.txt
git commit -m "Remove filename.txt"
git push
```

---

# Remove a Folder

```bash
git rm -r folder_name
git commit -m "Remove folder_name"
git push
```

---

# Keep a File on Your Computer but Remove It from GitHub

```bash
git rm --cached filename.txt
git commit -m "Stop tracking filename.txt"
git push
```

---

# Keep a Folder on Your Computer but Remove It from GitHub

```bash
git rm -r --cached folder_name
git commit -m "Stop tracking folder_name"
git push
```

---

# Check Repository Status

```bash
git status
```

---

# View Commit History

```bash
git log
```

---

# View Configured Remote Repository

```bash
git remote -v
```

---

# Clone an Existing GitHub Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPOSITORY.git
```

---

# Pull the Latest Changes from GitHub

```bash
git pull origin main
```

---

# View Available Branches

```bash
git branch
```

---

# Create a New Branch

```bash
git checkout -b branch_name
```

---

# Switch to Another Branch

```bash
git checkout branch_name
```

---

# Merge a Branch into the Current Branch

```bash
git merge branch_name
```

---

# Delete a Local Branch

```bash
git branch -d branch_name
```

---

# Delete a Remote Branch

```bash
git push origin --delete branch_name
```
